Claude 4.8 on 2026-06-30 at ~10:45: Started iteration 17 (copied from 16). All four parts are done and rendered-checked.

1. Cone — widened. In drawCast the bright cone was tangent to the INNER boundary; I retargeted the main beam to the OUTER boundary (outer.half = asin(rOut/d)), so it now spans the whole arc the point sees, with a fainter inner lobe left in to keep the centre brighter than the (grazing) edges. The interior-safety mechanism is the radial reach cap (reach = d - rIn): the whole inner hole sits at least d - rIn from any exterior point, so a cone capped at that radius can NEVER spill into the bowl whatever its aperture — that cap is untouched, so widening is safe. Verified with a deterministic capture (dragged a point to a fixed exterior spot): the beam fans wider and grazes the outer wall, and the bowl stays clean.

2. Ring message — sharper. Bumped the letters' supersample target 3x -> 4x device px (sharper antialiasing), nudged the font from 0.35 -> 0.40 of the ring thickness, and opened the letter-spacing 0.06 -> 0.085 so the glyphs stop crowding. Before/after close-ups confirm bigger, cleaner, better-separated letters.

3. Legibility of the gold text — FOUR runnable variants, differing ONLY in styles.css, in sources/iteration17/:
   - opt1_larger    — bigger gold headings.
   - opt2_contour   — a subtle dark contour (depth/emboss).
   - opt3_deepgold  — a deeper text-gold (var --gold-text #8f6207) decoupled from the bright motif gold; motifs stay bright, text reads easily. My recommendation; it is also what the iteration root currently uses.
   - opt4_glow      — bright gold wrapped in a soft dark glow-halo (luminous, on-theme).
   Each folder is fully runnable (own styles.css; index.html copy; main.js + assets symlinked to the iteration root). Open optN/index.html to compare.

Content externalization (i18n). The page's words now live in two editable files, assets/content.en.js and assets/content.es.js — each a plain window.CONTENT_<LANG> map of data-i18n key -> text, loaded by their own <script> tags before main.js (no fetch, so it still works from file:// and under the render). index.html is now pure structure: every translatable node carries data-i18n and is filled by main.js from the active language; the inline copies are stripped so each string lives in exactly one place. I also keyed the prose that wasn't translatable before (the two paper titles, the CiTIUS org line, the two Spanish degrees + their org lines), so the files hold essentially all the page's words. Proper names, dates and GPAs stay inline. Trade-off noted to Jonatan: with the text externalized, the raw HTML no longer carries the words for a no-JS view — happy to keep an inline English fallback if he prefers.

Not wrapping up (no close call): no interaction md / gallery shot yet, and the screenshot stays where he put it until wrap-up. Awaiting his pick among the four.


